u can imagine the responses I got from people.  Everything from good luck to Sev can't be camped to just laughter.  Even a few tells stating they would help.  After about 6-7 hours Sev poped.<br>
<br>
I am a member in good standing in a middle tier guild (Twilight Avengers of Prexus).  My guild mates knew what I was doing and why so they started to arrive quickly.  The Leaders in my guild knew how important it was to me and started to help.  After about 45 minutes we tried Sev the first time and wiped.  Rezzed and reset near FoB and beat him.<br>
<br>
This all happened a few months ago and a few things have changed since then but some valuable points can still be learned here.  First and foremost be stubborn but polite.  The polite will cut down interference and maybe get you some help.  Second if you are in a guild work with the Leaders in the guild for support if you can.  I had three or more people from four different guilds come and help, including a MB wizard though he did not have MB up for Sev.  This all happened during fairly heavy play times so it is possible to get Sev without paying an outrageous sum of plat to someone wearing a robe.  Just be stubborn but polite.<br>
